other_tests.findings: The patient had mild difficulties with attention and vigilance, as well as difficulties with some tasks of working memory. Vocabulary, nonverbal reasoning, and reading skills were all well above expected levels.

The patient had limited ocular function, including impaired smooth pursuit movements, saccades, convergence, and accommodation, and impaired vestibular function. Diagnosis of benign paroxysmal positional vertigo (BPPV) was made.
other_tests.changes_over_time: By the patient's second appointment, the BPPV had resolved and other treatments for vestibular and ocular impairment and exertion intolerance were initiated.
